== Surrounding Environment ==
The Nagaoka Hyakuana Kofun is situated in the northern part of [[:en:Utsunomiya|Utsunomiya]], at the southwestern foothills of the {{ill|Utsunomiya Hills|ja|宇都宮丘陵|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Utsunomiya Hills|qq=}}, near {{ill|Tomatsuriyama|ja|戸祭山|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tomatsuriyama|qq=|1=Mount Tomatsuri|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11496593}}. The site is located on a plateau flanked by the {{ill|Tagawa River (Tone River System)|ja|田川|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tagawa River (Tone River System)|qq=}} and the {{ill|Kamagawa River|ja|釜川|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamagawa River|qq=|1=Kama River|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11648095}}. The surrounding area features several other tumuli and ancient sites, including the {{ill|Yaguchiyama Kofun|lt=Yaguchiyama Kofun|lt=Taniguchiyama Kofun|ja|谷口山古墳|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taniguchiyama Kofun|qq=}}, {{ill|Kitayama Kofun Cluster|ja|北山古墳群|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kitayama Kofun Cluster|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|qid=Q135490863}}, {{ill|Kawarazuka Kofun Group|lt=Kawarazuka Kofun Group|lt=Kawarazuka Kofun Cluster|ja|瓦塚古墳群|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kawarazuka Kofun Cluster|qq=}}, and the {{ill|Tomatsuri Ōtsuka Kofun|ja|戸祭大塚古墳|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tomatsuri Ōtsuka Kofun|qq=}}, as well as remains from the [[:en:Nara period|Nara period]], such as the {{ill|Suidōyama Tile Kiln Site|ja|水道山瓦窯跡|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suidōyama Tile Kiln Site|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}. These sites are linked by the {{ill|Toyosato Mahoroba Road|ja|豊郷まほろばの道|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toyosato Mahoroba Road|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}.

The tombs are surrounded by greenery, including [[:en:Quercus serrata|Quercus serrata]] and [[:en:Quercus acutissima|Quercus acutissima]]. The area is Historic Site1 as the Nagaoka Green Conservation Area by Tochigi Prefecture<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.pref.tochigi.lg.jp/d04/30jikannti/10nagaoka.html|title=10 Nagaoka Green Conservation Area|website=Tochigi Prefecture |accessdate=2024-11-11}}</ref>.

Urbanization has increased in the surrounding area with the development of the {{ill|Utsunomiya Ring Road|ja|宇都宮環状道路|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Utsunomiya Ring Road|qq=|1=Utsunomiya Ring Road|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11449792}}.

